For this task, I used Canva to create an infographic on digital literacy. Canva is a user-friendly design tool that provides various templates, icons, and design elements, making it easy to create visually appealing content. My design includes key topics such as the meaning of digital literacy, useful digital tools for students, safe internet practices, professional online presence, and email etiquette. Each section is presented with short points and icons to make the information easy to understand and visually engaging.

While creating the infographic, I found it interesting to explore different layouts and color combinations to make the design attractive. One difficulty I faced was organizing the content in a limited space while keeping it clear and readable. However, using Canva templates helped me manage the layout effectively. This activity improved my creativity and design skills, and also enhanced my understanding of digital literacy concepts. It will be helpful for presentations and academic projects in the future.
